ings":["From the Old Celtic intensive prefix <i>an-</i> + <i>cār</i> ‘love’ + the noun suffix <i>-ad</i>. This was the name of the mother of the 12th-century chronicler  Giraldus Cambrensis  (‘Gerald the Welshman’). In the <i>Mabinogi</i>, Angharad Golden Hand at first rejects Peredur's suit, but later falls in love with him when he comes back as the unknown Mute Knight. The name has been strongly revived in Wales since the 1940s, borne, for example, by the actress  Angharad Rees  (  1949-2012 )."],"variants":[]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Angharad ferch Madog was born about 1412, in Montgomeryshire, Wales, her father, Madog ap Cadwgon, was 28 and her mother, Mrs. Madog ap Cadwgon, was 24. She had at least 2 sons with Gruffudd  \"Fychan\" ap Gruffudd."},"et":{"ABT    1412–":"umbes 1412–Surnud","1412–Female":"1412–Surnud","1398–Male":"1398–Surnud","1386–Male":"1386–Surnud","1434–Male":"1434–Surnud","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","ABT    1412":"umbes 1412","ABT    1434":"umbes 1434","1434":"1434","1412":"1412","1398":"1398","1386":"1386","about 1434":"umbes 1434","1390":"1390","Wales":"Wales","of,,Shropshire,England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomeryshire, Wales"},"fi":{"ABT    1412–":"noin 1412–Kuollut","1412–Female":"1412–Kuollut","1398–Male":"1398–Kuollut","1386–Male":"1386–Kuollut","1434–Male":"1434–Kuollut","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","ABT    1412":"noin 1412","ABT    1434":"noin 1434","1434":"1434","1412":"1412","1398":"1398","1386":"1386","about 1434":"noin 1434","1390":"1390","Wales":"Wales","of,,Shropshire,England":"Shropsh